-- Deutsche Bank Says Former North Asia Investment Head Has Left
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   G a r v e y
-- 2012-03-19T08:00:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/deutsche-bank-says-former-north-asia-investment-head-has-left.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ’s former Hong
Kong-based head of investment advisory for North Asia, Bill Tsang, left the bank on Jan. 30, according to the German lender.  He had worked for Deutsche Bank for eight years, Terence
Ng, a spokesman for the bank, said on March 16 by telephone from
Singapore.  Tsang was hired as head of investment products in Asia
outside of Japan by  Nomura Holdings Inc. (8604) ’s wealth management
division on Feb. 1, Jonathan Williams, Nomura’s Singapore-based
spokesman, said last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
